caption: This place has The Best Sushi in chicago !!!  The chef has unique flavor combinations, amazing quality of all the fish and ingredients.  The place is small so plan ahead.  BYOB.   Definitely an amazing flavor experience !!

We’ve been enjoying sushi from Toro for over 10 years and the quality of the fish and service has always been amazing. Cannot say enough good things about Mitch, the staff, and the food and service. It’s been great we have been able to support them through delivery during the pandemic and hope to be back soon!

We’ve now tried takeout here on two occasions. Toro was recommended by a friend since we noticed a decline in fish quality at sushi restaurants during the pandemic. On that front, Toro continues to have high quality fish. The first time ordering with them, Toro messed up our order and sent us some of the wrong rolls. We called and they offered a discount on a future order over the phone, but never actually sent us the discount. We tried them again tonight, and this time our sushi was missing sauces, had components that weren’t listed (wasabi in the roll, lemon flavored tobiko), and as a result just didn’t taste that good.
Delicious food, love their hand rolls . My go to spot anytime I’m craving sushi :)

The portions are supper small, the food itself is decent. For the bento box C employee told me soup was included so i canceled my 2 orders of miso soups so i did not end up with 4 soups since i ordered 2 bento boxes, turns out I did not receive any soup in my order
They gave me wrongdoers. Had to go back and when I pointed out there error they gave zero apology. Absolutely Zero Fs given. At least at McDonald's when this has happened they say sorry.
username: JM JM JM JM JM JM

caption: 10 persons working and taking like 3 hours for one order too much laziness!!!

How anyone can rate this place less than 5 stars is beyond me. It's perfection. Kamakaze and sunshine- just explosions of deliciousness. This is one of the main things I miss since having moved from Chicago (other than the view).
Delicious. Pick up was right on time.

You guys really need to figure out a pick up proceeds during phase 3/4. There is no clear process anyone is supposed to follow — someone people wait in line, others barge in; sometimes the food isn’t ready when the person is inside but they won’t leave — it’s just chaos. Super long wait time; love this place and used to come often but won’t in the future unless this is solved. Not worth the time and frustration
The Awesome roll and three musketeers were really good! And the vegetable gyozas as well, one of my favorite sushi places in Chicago
Mitch is always welcoming & fish is always fresh
Best sushi rolls I've ever had! I'm from MN, but I go to Toro at least twice every time I'm in Chicago!
Great sushi
this is my favorite sushi restaurant in the world.
Best sushi in Chicago! BYOB
Excellent and yummy food, I loved the character the place has, and the employees were helpful. I will surely visit here next time.
One of the best sushi places if not the best. Especially for that price range. Everything we had was delicious, can't wait to come back 🍥 😍
Amazing

My FAVORITE sushi restaurant! Happy chefs and staff, great prices, always clean (and very busy!) is -this place is a Lincoln Park jem♡ A+ We ordered the Crazy Horse, escolar, Spider roll and the california roll...
The service is constantly prompt, excellent character, very welcoming employees. Will visit here again when I arrive in town.
Red dragon is great! Seaweed salad was excellent too. Love this place and the workers. Will be returning.
Excellent food service and price. Couldn't ask for more.

Fresh sushi and friendly Chef Mitch make this spot my wife's and my favorite sushi restaurant in Chicago. Arrive before 5:30 to guarantee a table. Our standby choices include the shrimp tempura, Philadelphia roll, yellow tail, spicy tuna and fried salmon skin hand rolls.
Some of my favorite sushi in Licoln Park! Tastes great and is reasonably priced. Restaurant is tight though and anticipate a wait if you are going on the weekend.
Overpriced .. quality not bad

Really good sushi and such quick service! I came in on a Saturday around 6pm and was seated right away. This was my second attempt coming on a Saturday because once the wait was 2 hours when I came around 8pm so my advice is to go early as they do not take reservations!! The appetizers and sushi came out really quickly and I was in and out in under an hour. Very friendly staff and sushi chefs.
Toro is the absolute best!
Mitch is the best sushi chef in the city. You're making a mistake by not experiencing it

Toro sushi has been a staple for me for many years. It’s a small restaurant so getting a table on a busy night may involve a wait, but it’s worth it. I also order carryout from there quite often. It is my favorite sushi place in Lincoln Park because it is very high quality with low frills. The super white crunch roll, spring blossom roll, kamikaze hand roll and hamachi hand rolls are personal favorites. The nigiri is also great and reasonably priced. Overall, great and friendly environment and awesome sushi - I highly recommend.
Favorite sushi in Chicago.  Original rolls, high quality sushi.
Service was very attentive, attention to detail was impeccable. Will definitely visit again
Just two words: incredible sushi. Super fresh and super delicious.
Really creative rolls, fresh fish, byob, and friendly atmosphere...has become one of my favorite spots now
Amazing sushi place - its a small space, but nice for locals and those that love sushi. Would definitely recommend if you're looking for a sushi place in the area
Best Sushi in Chicago! Small BYOB place, no reservations. Can be a wait. Mitch and his staff take the time and put in the effort for quality sushi and experience.

This is one of the best sushi spots in all or Chicago. Been going for years, it's a very small place so be prepared for a wait after 6p or so on most days. We always call ahead to see how long the wait will be.
Speaks for itself.

Nice concept for a set price with a cute bowl size that is to go or dine in. It's in the Chicago section with other restaurants as a healthier and fun alternative. Choose your base and they create the bowl and place in the fire and bam your bowl is ready to eat! The noodles were my favorite!

One of the best sushi places I’ve ever been to. Spectacular fat and juicy salmon. Amazing white tuna. Delicious maki rolls and special rolls. Great hand rolls. I could eat here every weekend. I wish the sit down area wasn’t so tight, but it’s okay... not worthy of dinging a star. 5 stars regardless.
Can get expensive, but it tastes great.
Small space with ok service, took 5 mins for me to get a waiter to our table.
Food was great, the bento box will fill you up!
Best sushi not near the ocean
Food is super tasty and decently priced. Loved the salad and spicy tuna tempura roll!!

Our favorite sushi/Japanese cuisine spot in town. We've tried many Japanese restaurant in Chicago and Toro is the only place that we would revisit for sushi. They also have the best unagi that we've had in Chicago. Highly recommend all of their temakis.

Fantastic Sushi. Always fresh with great service. The owners are usually behind the counter assembling sushi. Great people! Don't think about it, just go eat there! My reviews are for the best of the best. Like & Share.
FABULOUS sushi, wait staff very friendly and attentive. Atmosphere is very quaint and prices are extremely reasonable! A must visit if you are a sushi lover!
Best in chicago

YUUUMMM. Love the sushi here. Lots of great selections for rolls. They are great with gluten free options- even have a gluten free version of soft shell crab. There’s no reservations so hope for the best and prepare for the wait. It’s worth it!

Worth the wait! Toro has well thought out, unique roll options. For example, I'd highly recommend the kamikaze rolls! It's served with the rolls in a circular pyramid and topped with  fish kani, sunflower seeds, tobiko, and spicy mayo! Unlike anything I've ever had and I spent about a year in the Bay area of California. Make sure to stop by the liquor store next door to pickup a bottle of wine, Toro is BYOB!

Friend suggested we catch up here. Looks like a hole in the wall but whatever, I won’t suggest going elsewhere. Holy molly this sushi place is on top of their game. Generous portions. Nice staff. Will be back.
Quality Sushi. BYOB. Friendly staff.
You will never have anything better -

Bruh..this place is iconic .. been coming for years ..favourite special maki rolls still include Arizona, Kamikaze.. the nigiri and sushi are great as well.. it's BYOB and in Lincoln park ..fantastic location.. great staff and service ..
best every week sushi in Chicago period. Nigiri + sashimi = <3
Good sushi too small for intimate ambiance
Excellent neighborhood sushi restaurant. Consistently great!
Great sushi. Awesome service. Thanks Mitch for the great sushi!
a must visit if you like sushi. i encourage you to set at the bar and meet the super friendly chef, Mitch!!
Hard to find good sushi around Chicago, but I finally found one. A lot of choices to choose from and I doubt any will fail you. Very reasonably priced too!
It's a pretty good neighborhood hole in the wall kinda spot. Very friendly chef and people. You might run into regulars there. They seem to get quite a lot of take out orders.
One of the best sushi spots in Lakeview.

Always order the real wasabi. It is extremely delicious and it is fun to do the taste test comparison. Also, the dinner bento boxes are huge. Great deal on the amount of food. Quality fish and the yellowtail sashimi was outstanding.
Fish was just ok. Overall not great, but pretty good value
Cozy little place with excellent food. The place is small, you are very close to everyone, this is not an issue as everyone is nice and friendly. Did I mention it's BYOB.

Truly a local gem within Lincoln Park. Sushi is fresh and made with quality ingredients. Ordered the mussel appetizer and a few rolls, and was not disappointed. One of my favorite sushi places with a really unique BYOB atmosphere. Great service, great food, & 5/5!
Best Sushi in all of Chi! There is no competition! From appetizer to sushi all is fresh and amazing !
Love this place. I wish they were open earlier hours during the week.

Overall: The inevitable wait is worth the quality. Great tasting sushi, much better than anything else I've had in the city. Definitely will come back when the craving hits again.  The good: Best sushi I have had in Chicago, and the best I've ever had in the states. Only sushi I've had that has been better has been in Japan. Reasonable prices too, for sushi anyway. Humble environment with great chefs. Oh, and its BYOB  The bad: The waits are LONG. Plan to put your name down and come back. They don't take reservations either. You will most likely have to wait.  Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 8/10 Food: 9/10
Probably the best casual sushi place around.

I've gone to most of the really "fancy" sushi restaurants in Chicago and Toro's sushi is definitely just as good (actually, even better!). Their specialty rolls we ordered were $16-$18 each but well worth it. I love the fact the restaurant is byob!!
Sushi is subpar

[Updated 2018.07.24] - Love Toro sushi.  Mitch is awesome and very friendly.  Lots of custom sushi rolls which showcases his creativity and flavors.  Be prepared to wait 1-2 hours if you get here after 6pm. Put your name in and then walk down the street to DOC's wine bar and enjoy a glass or bottle of wine or Duke's Chicago bar.  Party's of 4 are ideal as the place is small.  My favorite rolls: Oh My God, Sunny, & spicy tuna roll. This is my favorite sushi place in Chicago.

Delicious, cozy sushi place! It is smaller so make sure you call ahead or just be comfortable with a little wait. It is well worth it! Vegetarian rolls were very imaginative which is typically hard to find. Everything rolling out of the sushi bar looked amazing! Hand rolls, maki, you name it. Deep. Fried. Green. Tea. Ice-cream. No other words needed, so good. BYOB, there is a small convenience store right across the street so it’s easy to grab something cold and bring it in if you aren’t prepared.
The food here was SO good!
The sushi was great. The place is too crowded and the food is slightly pricey. Paid about 30$ for a maki and a half.

My go-to sushi place in Chicago. Cheap and delicious sushi made better with its BYOB policy. When I sit at the bar, the chef often has us try even more types of sushi for free. Go early to avoid a wait!
The best in town
Mitch is the man.
Subpar sushi. Long wait
I called ahead and they had a table waiting for us! Delicious and great prices.
Best in Chicago
Love this place

This is the best place in town for your Saturday bento box. Sushi chef Mitch has been taking care of me for over a decade, greeting me every visit and sometimes sending samples of special off menu items to try. The fish is always fresh and the service is prompt. Toro is my happy place!
Mitch is the best, fist bump
Great neighborhood sushi spot, casual and reasonably priced for quality. Gets busy. BYOB!
Best sushi I’ve ever had.
Good Sushi
Kamikaze is so amazing! Creative delicious menu!
911 rolls were awesome

The sushi is good, it’s not amazing but it’s good. The space is small and it’s not fancy. We were seated in the alley leading to the back. It wasn’t the best of experiences. There is usually a long wait on the weekend. So unless you’re willing to wait I would not recommend this place. There are better new sushi places in the neighborhood. As a lakeview/ Lincoln park resident it’s one of those places that you have to try at least once, but that’s where I d draw the line.
Mitch is the man. This place has heat sushi. Get the sunny roll.
Amazing sushi!
Best sushi in Chicago, hands down. Sunny roll is #1
This is the best sushi on Chicago. I always order sashimi and have yet to find anyone who beats Mitch.

Sushi is good, good place... But waiting an hour just to eat I think it is too much. Service is great and food also, but a bit expensive and, as I said, sushi is sushi and there are plenty of places to have good sushi. But good place 👍👍👍
Showed up. Packed. Dude said I am next. Couple came in. And chick sat them. Then chick came to me and said I would be next. Over priced as well. Guess I am too old for this place. Too busy and small.
they came to our office the other day and taught us how to make sushi... it was all very delicious and he is entertaining.
Above average sushi, relatively quick service and surprisingly cheap.
Top notch sushi and still my favorite maki rolls I've ever had.
Amazing food, But call before if no you have to wait. Enjoy
Best place for sushi. Amazing staff and care for the customer.
Best Sushi ever... Try Kamikaze
Tako when it is in season is amazing
100% DANK™
Hidden gem.  Authentic friendly and quality.

There are soooo many trendy ramen restaurants around, Toro is just one of many. The place is clean modern and very nice. But the ramen it self is nothing special the flavor is acceptable, the noodles could be more chewy and more plentiful. It's hard to compare to the really good ones in Tokyo or even Cali. Wish I could be more positive.
Best sushi in Chicago!

Fantastic sushi and BYOB -- a combo that's hard to beat. We had 3 specialty rolls and one maki roll, and all of them were outstanding. Our bill was about $45 which, considering we also had a bottle of wine, is a steal for a sushi dinner of this quality. It's small and there was a wait, but they take your cell number so you can go out and grab a drink without having to stand around waiting in close quarters. I'll make a point of coming back.

Poor experience, rather overrated.  Had one terrific roll with octopus (forget the name), but the rest of our rolls and the appetizer were pretty bland and not worth the wait.  Told 45min wait when we arrived, came back 50min later only to get two seats at the bar.  Hostess called us after we left (2hrs after checking in) to say our table was ready.  Had to flag a waitress to order after waiting several minutes once finally seated.  Very loud at our seating area and slightly obnoxious.  They don't take Amex.  All in all, not a 5 star sushi restaurant in my humble opinion.
Amazing food, service was ok... the table maintenance was poor.
Incredible sushi, great hole-in-the-wall feel, good service. BYOB

Great for dining in and takeout.  I've enjoyed sushi for years now and have reached a point where I can't eat just any sushi. This place passes the test.  Great, creative rolls and the nigiri/sashimi is high quality (so the sushi pieces are great on their own).  Cozy and friendly atmosphere is great for a date but , Toro is popular with good reason, so get there early or expect about a 15-20 minute wait.  We've had the Sunny, O, El Fuego, Southern Gals, and Jilly Bean (that I recall) and enjoyed all of them - loved Sunny and O.  Easy 5 stars.
Best sush in Chicago!!

BYOB and no "cork fee".  The sushi is awesome and the service is always great as well.  The only "issue" is getting a table during peak hours.  The place is small.  Not cramped, just small.  Therefore, during ideal dinning hours, it becomes difficult to get a table.
Must try the hand roll.
Quite simply the best sushi in town.

Fantastic Sushi without a snobbish atmosphere, very casual. I brought my gf here for her birthday a d while visually the fanciest amazing food, and definitely worth a visit. Your money goes to good ingredients and talents Sushi masters rather then spent on décor.
What great sushi! Everything was very fresh and inventive. I really enjoyed my meal here. I definitely will be returning! Order the Jalapeno Poppers-You will NOT be disappointed!

This place serves the best sushi I've ever had! I now compare all the sushi places I try to Toro sushi and none has surpassed this place yet. The sushi here is very flavorful and fresh, with perfect stuffing-to-rice ratio. The rice is also perfect, not too soft/mushy nor too hard. It's kinda sad how many other sushi places do not get the rice right. Very reasonable prices too.
The best sushi. Mitch does a great job
Amazing!  Try crazy horse roll!
Best neighborhood sushi spot.  New menu (as of summer 2016) with more innovative sushi roll combinations but also new prices. I'm a big Ikura fan and theirs is high quality.
Loved it! Great, fresh sushi and the chef was very interactive and friendly, taking the time to ask what I liked and introducing me to new things.  Exactly what sushi should be.
Ehhh stupid Americans..... This restaurant is OK.
Best sushi in Chicago! Even though you will have to wait for a table, it is well worth the wait. Amazing rolls and BYOB. Try the kamikaze roll!

Food: 4 Decor: 3 Service: 4  After driving an hour all the way from Waukegan and getting rejected earlier in the week, I decided to come back here with a party of 6 for dinner shortly after they opened, around 5:30pm.  We were able to get a seat without a problem. All the tables were filled by 6pm, and the wait started getting long by 6:30pm, so arrive earlier to beat the wait. Parking is street, so good luck.  Everyone ordered at least two rolls, which was about enough food.  1. OMG Pretty good. Some of my friends agreed that it was probably the best roll out of the 8+ we ordered.  2. Kamikaze Very good. Toppings were delicious, and it had the perfect amount of spiciness.  3. Arizona Very good. Definitely in my top three favorite rolls.  4. Crazy horse  5. Al fuego Pretty good. Couldn't really taste the difference between this one and some of the other rolls.  6. Green tea ice cream Very good. Generous scoop of green tea ice cream with some chocolate syrup and powdered sugar. Green tea wasn't overbearing at all.  My friends who had the salmon nigiri said it was very good.  Overall, very good sushi. Rolls are around $12-15 each, and there is 20% gratuity for parties of 5 or more. My total was about $33 after tax/tip.

Great sushi for a decent price! The staff is extremely friendly. Be ready to wait or maybe even order it to go as the place is small and jam packed from open to close. They are fast and great at what they do! And there's talk of a new location in downtown that will be open for lunch during the week!

Great sushi and BYOB. Limit of one wine bottle per 2 people or the equivalent with no hard liquor. Everything was fresh and orders came out very quickly. Be prepared to wait because they have a small space. If it was larger, I think I would give the place a 5
Best sushi in Chicago, the place is VERY small though.
One of my favorites sushi joints in the area
Some of the best quality, most creative rolls I've had. Try and get there right at 5. Very small.
Probably the best sushi I ever had. BYOB. Come before the place opens otherwise you'll need to wait a long time for a table.
Really good sushi and pretty good service. Reasonable prices but really limited hours. Get there the minute they open or you'll be waiting 45-60 minutes or eating elsewhere.
Delicious variety of rolls with BYOB option.

My personal training clients, Jeremy and Nicole, have been raving about Toro for the last two years, and I regretfully waited until this past Sunday to stop in. The food was unbelievable!!!! The rolls were incredibly fresh and the service was stellar. My mouth is still watering thinking about each of the 4 rolls we tried! Without a doubt, you have to stop in and visit Mitch!

My experience with this restaurant began and ended regretfully. I called ahead to see if they took reservations, and an incredibly impolite hostess informed me that they did not. They would not hold a table. Not deterred, I took a cab from my Gold Coast apartment to Lincoln Park to this place and there was a table open when I got there. They wouldn't give it to me. There was no line, and yet I was informed that the fictitious "waiting list" was such that I would have to wait an hour and a half. There was no one waiting. I have never been treated so poorly by a sushi restaurant before, and I will never go back. The staff lied, and was incredibly discourteous. I went to another sushi restaurant in Lincoln Park called "Nori." They seated me immediately, and the quality was very high. Ordinarily, I don't like to complain, but the experience with the wait staff at Toro was so bad I would be remise if I did not write a review. There are excellent sushi restaurants all over Chicago, and with service this horrible, it amazes me that they remain in business. An absolute disgrace to Chicago's sushi scene.

I wouldn't really put it as a 1 star if this places hasn't have the high rating it doesn't deserve. All the people who gave it 5 stars are probably just people who never really had real sushi. Here is why:  The chef is passionate about what he does, somewhat cocky about it too, for such an attitude you'd expect the sushi to taste good, but it is just alright.  the wasabi tasted really bland  their soy sauce is not even made right, they just bought store bought soy sauce and pour it into a jar and used it!!! Let me tell you, the soy sauce for real sushi is not just some store bought soy sauce! there is more ingredients to it.  Their rice taste kind of weird.....but i don't care much for rice anyway  The only good thing about this place is the fact that their fish pieces are larger than other places most sushi restaurants make the fish cut same size as the rice under it but this place do give larger than normal cuts, so that is a pro. Will I go back? maybe....but i would probably not order their sushi.....perhaps their maki is a bit better but i'd have to try and see  ps. their miso soup is really really salty....
Fresh beyond fresh. Fish is amazing quality, and sushi bar staff is super friendly. try lunch on a weekday to avoid the line.
Best sushi place in chi town

The only negative thing about this place is that you're almost guaranteed to have to wait before being seated regardless of what time you go. The good news is that Molly's cupcakes is just a couple of doors down! The sushi is fresh and the service is phenomenal. Also, it's BYOB!

Toro Sushi is one of the best sushi places I've been to in a long time.  We ordered the Salmon Crunch, Spicy Tuna, Spicy California, and Volcano Rolls. I highly recommend the Volcano Rolls (SPOILER ALERT: They come out with a sparkler attached to the plate). All of the rolls were delicious.  Much like other sushi places in the city, they were BYOB, which is convenient as there was a liquor store just down the street. It's a small restaurant, so seating is tight, but the sound level stays relatively low and it doesn't distract from any discussions you want to have at your table.  There can be a long wait depending on when you go due to the small size of the restaurant, however we were able to get in really easy with just two people. It's a great place for a date, and I highly recommend checking it out.
Some of the best sushi in the city, but be prepared to wait. It's a BYO and they don't accept reservations. Their sashimi and nigiri roll combination platters are delicious.

The sushi might be the best in Chicago.  You can't go wrong with BYOB.  The service is great.  The only reason I wouldn't give this five stars is because it is tiny and always crowded.  The secret is out, and it is really hard to relax and enjoy a meal when it is really crowded and cramped and the next people waiting for a table (there are no reservations) are sitting in the doorway staring at you.
The best sushi i ever had, OMG and That's how we roll are my favorite, i can't get enough of this place

Heard so much about this place, had to check it out. So glad I did, the sushi is nothing short of AMAZING! So fresh, love the specialty rolls they offer. It is always a wait, as it is a small place, but it's worth it, and the size actually adds to the ambiance. Will be back here soon!
Good sushi and great sashimi. They have both simple rolls as well as complex flavorful rolls.  Def coming back.

If you like to fist bump, come to this establishment.  The owner, Mitch, loves to give a little fist bump and finger tip tiddle to all his patrons.  Honestly, this place rules--it's some of the best sushi in Chicago.  I would give it 5 stars if they had more seating.  If you go here, you should expect to wait.  Toro is BYOB, so feel free to bring a bottle of wine.  I highly recommend you stay away from bringing white wine, or beer because you're going to wait for a table.  The sushi is really interesting, and they have tons of specialty rolls.   This place rules.
Amazing sushi
It's good every time. But please go somewhere else because Toro is mine!

Mitch the owner is so down to earth and nice to his customers. The lunch special on Fridays is a great deal and lots of food for your money. I wish the restaurant was a little bigger because it gets crowded. Delicious and fresh.

This is my favorite place for sushi in Chicago. Albeit it's small, it's worth the wait. BYOB and the prices aren't through the roof. My girlfriend and I love sitting and the bar and chatting with Mitch. He's the man and puts together some amazing dishes

No wonder so many people wait over an hour to eat at this tiny restaurant....the sushi is AMAZING!!  After years of wanting to go here, I finally get the chance and I can't wait to go back!  Toro is definitely worth the hour wait.  The sushi is so mouthwateringly delicious and so fresh!  The combinations were quite interesting and the prices were very reasonable for what you get.  Even though the tiny place was packed, service was friendly and attentive.  Also, I love the bowl of  free edamame!
I LOVE THE SUSHI HERE!!! GO HERE!!! You will enjoy it!!!
Great sushi spot on Clark. Very small, so usually very crowded. Mitch (the owner) is awesome and runs the show there. Get the Oh My God Roll, you won't regret it. Edamame is also really good.

Chef Mitch is my hero!!!  I have never had sushi I have wanted to rave about more in my life.  Chef is creative in ways that Chicago hasn't seen at for sushi in years.  Its a small place and it is always worth the wait.  BYOB is a great plus.

Toro is the best sushi place in the city... hands down.... fresh, quality fish and large pieces for the price.  Mitch is awesome! Sit at the sushi bar and he greets you with a "Japanese pound" of the fish and teaches you about everything you could ever want to know about sushi!  Always a wait, but that is a sign of a fantastic restaurant... well worth the wait.... every time.
The best sushi in LP! I love the energy and Mitch is amazing! My favorite roll is the Kamakaze! There are no reservations allowed so the wait can be long but for sure worth every penny!

Most of the staff seemed very nice. the decor is very comfortable and clean. The overall experience was good. We had the tempura and california. It wasn't the best, but I have had incredible sushi before. Good for the price.
i thought it as pretty awesome and i Liked it
Great sushi! Everything I have ever had is amazing, fresh, and innovative

This is my favorite sushi restaurant in the city! Without a doubt there will be a wait, but it is worth it! Get the Ahi Salad Special Roll! It is my favorite and nothing else like it! BYOB so you can get your booze on too! AMAZE BALLS.
I thought it was the best sushi!!! Spicy tuna roll was amazing!!!!
Best Sushi in Chicago.  Get there early, because it's always packed.  Well worth the wait.  Give them your number and grab a beer down the street at Franks.  You will not regret it.
Best sushi in Chicago! Always a long wait, but it's worth it!

Toro sushi is the best sushi in Chicago by far! Mitch and the whole staff are friendly, the food is fresh, incredible, and there are rolls there that you wont find anywhere else! I would recommend Toro to any out of towners, locals, and anyone looking for a great different place to try sushi. Beware they do not have tables suitable to large parties and also they do not take reservations, you can go and if there is a wait you put your name down and go to the wine bar a few doors down while you wait for a table.
Best sushi in town! Always great service and quality.. tiny restaurant but the wait is never too extreme.

(Translated by Google) The best sushi I've ever eaten. Good straight through, nothing to complain about!  Maybe you can queue a bit for a table.  (Original) Den bästa sushin jag någonsin ätit. Bra rakt igenom, inget att klaga på!  Kanske får du köa lite för ett bord.

A small understated restaurant. The sushi is some of the best i have had. An amazing selection of rolls. BYOB. Expect to wait to get a table, they do call back so you can go for a drink near by. Amazing price for truly top end food.

Great sushi at a great price. The restaurant does not take reservations and they were always 40 minutes behind on weekdays so it is hard to time a date correctly, but if you can make it I would recommend it
BYOB. Some of the best sushi I've had in Chicago and people know it, always busy on the weekends.
Best sushi place in town. If only it had decent hours and seating
sushi is great at this place. super great service
Super GReat food!

I've been to Toro Sushi on 2 different occasions, each of them being very excellent. With a bottle of sake in hand, my girlfriend and I ordered an assortment of rolls. They were all delicious! I always order dragon rolls, so we got 1 of those.  Whatever you order, everything tastes excellent and is very fresh. Service is great too. We had to wait a little bit, but they took down our cell number so we were free to walk around the neighborhood while we waited, which was nice of them.  HIGHLY recommended.
Delicious, fresh sushi. The chef is a great guy and keeps you entertained. Make sure to arrive ahead of time because there is usually a wait.
not so good survice. good food. awesome people. great sushi
Very fresh sushi and reasonable prices for some amazing rolls. Major plus is that it is BYOB.
Best sushi in town!  Services is awesome!  The servers are there if you need them and leave you alone if you want to chill!  The seafood is fresh.
good sushi
Hands down the best sushi around. Every roll is fab, el fuego and kamikaze two of the best.

This is a really quaint sushi spot located on Clark street. They don't take reservations over the phone and they are always busy. I suggest you go early to get in before the crowd. The staff is wonderful and Mitch is always fabulous. Try to sit up by the sushi bar. He and the other staff are so engaging. All the sushi is amazing.. you can't go wrong with any of them. Add this to your must go list in Chicago.
This small location is always busy as people crave the sushi.  The roles are fresh and the staff is very personable.
BYOB! Favorite Lincoln Park sushi bar.  If you are in the area this is a must.

Hand down the best hidden sushi spot in Chicago.  It is very small and quaint, but the ambience grounds you in the best sushi experience you will ever have.  After about 2 -3 rolls ( I was very hungry), I ended it with a fried green tea ice cream...AMAZING.  I never had anything like it before.  I would go back just for the ice cream! Make friends with the Chef...he might give you a few perks here and there.
If you can get a spot in this tiny restaurant - enjoy it! Some of the best, freshest sushi in Chicago - just wish the space was bigger!
Amazing sushi chef that is so concerned about quality that...well you'll have to ask him.  As the sign says, sushi does make better lovers.

No doubt about it. This place is where it's at. It's the only restaurant on the street that is packed. I waited 45 minutes for a single seat at the bar. But it's totally worth it cause I'm sitting right in front of Mitch. He's definitely a cool dude who makes a killer roll.
So far I'm impressed and I haven't even gotten my sushi yet

Still the best Sushi in Chicago.  I haven't been to this place in a long time, not living in the Chicago.  Moved back a few weeks ago and after trying a few different sushi places still got drawn back to this place.  Make sure you come in early, put your name, and go grab a pint in the neighborhood.  They will call your cell phone when your table is ready.  Highly recommended!
